---
import "./Approach.css";
---

<section class="questions-section">
    <div class="questions-container">
        <div class="questions-left">
            <div class="questions-header">
                <div class="questions-label">• WHY USE OUR SERVICE?</div>
                <h2>
                    Frequently Asked Questions<br />
                    About Kitchen Remodeling in Maryland
                </h2>
            </div>
            <div class="questions-faqs">
                <div class="faq-item expanded">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        How Much Does a Kitchen Remodel Cost in Maryland?
                        <span class="faq-icon">–</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        Kitchen remodeling costs in Maryland range from $12,000 to $50,000, depending on the size, materials, layout changes, and finishes.<br />
                        We offer free quotes tailored to your space and needs.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        How Long Does a Full Kitchen Remodel Take?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Can I Use My Kitchen During the Remodel?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        What’s Included in Your Kitchen Remodeling Services?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Do You Help with Kitchen Design and Material Selection?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="questions-right">
            <div class="questions-intro">
                Planning a kitchen remodel in Maryland? You’re not alone! We’ve answered the most common questions homeowners ask — from costs and permits to layouts and materials — so you can feel confident before starting your project.
            </div>
            <div class="questions-faqs">
                <div class="faq-item expanded">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Can You Remove Walls or Create an Open Concept Layout?
                        <span class="faq-icon">–</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        Absolutely. We specialize in open concept kitchen remodeling, including wall removal, space reconfiguration, and structural adjustments.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Do You Offer Custom Cabinets or Only Prefab Options?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Do You Provide Financing or Payment Plans?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Will You Handle Permits and Inspections?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Is Your Work Covered by a Warranty?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>